{
  "stem": "4113.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And to the east of us, all hell broke loose-- now, this didn't happen in our place-- for where the German armies entered, they now had organized their Sonderkommandos, the special commands, which were trained to kill Jews and Soviet functionaries, which--",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because, prior to that, there was lots of communication.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "People would smuggle over back and forth.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was very easy to go.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "People would go back and forth, you know.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] and as they marched in there, many people who were caught up by the German armies now in former eastern Poland, now Soviet territory, came back.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So came my cousin back, the one that survived Auschwitz, and my other cousin, a number of them.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "People came back.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[BACKGROUND NOISE] They wanted to come back to the German side even before that, believe it or not, because when the Germans were making-- were making a deal with Hitler to allow German nationals who lived in the eastern part of Poland and-- and in the Soviet Union-- to exchange them, you know, to bring them and let others go there, you know, Jews registered to come back, because it was relatively quiet.",
      "word_count": 73
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We used to write to them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We heard all the time from them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They all wanted to come back, because the-- this killing wasn't there.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "You see, they wanted to come home.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And as they registered, the Soviets took that the registration list, packed them on a train, and shipped them off to Siberia.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And that's-- my Uncle Joseph, with his family, was shipped off.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The one who is now in Australia, he stayed, but his sister was shipped off.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
